<elasticsearch_security_guide>
<title>ELASTICSEARCH SECURITY TESTING</title>

<critical>Elasticsearch is a distributed search and analytics engine widely used for logging, search, and data analysis. Security vulnerabilities include unauthenticated access, query injection, script execution, cluster manipulation, and data exposure. Many Elasticsearch instances are exposed without authentication, leading to massive data breaches.</critical>

<scope>
- Unauthenticated cluster access
- Query DSL injection
- Scripting and code execution
- Index and document manipulation
- Cluster configuration exposure
- API key and role security
- X-Pack/Security features bypass
- Snapshot and restore exploitation
</scope>

<methodology>
1. Identify Elasticsearch instances and versions.
2. Test for unauthenticated access to cluster APIs.
3. Enumerate indices, mappings, and data.
4. Probe for query injection in application searches.
5. Test script execution and dangerous features.
</methodology>

<reconnaissance>
<instance_discovery>
{% raw %}
# Default ports:
9200  # HTTP REST API
9300  # Transport protocol (internal)

# Discovery methods:
nmap -p 9200,9300 -sV target.com

# Shodan queries:
port:9200 elasticsearch
product:elasticsearch
elasticsearch country:US

# Common endpoints:
http://target:9200/
http://target:9200/_cluster/health
http://target:9200/_cat/indices

# Cloud services:
# AWS OpenSearch (formerly Elasticsearch Service)
# Elastic Cloud
# Azure Cognitive Search (Elasticsearch-compatible)
{% endraw %}
</instance_discovery>

<version_fingerprinting>
{% raw %}
# Get cluster information:
curl http://target:9200/

# Response reveals:
{
  "name": "node-1",
  "cluster_name": "elasticsearch",
  "cluster_uuid": "xxx",
  "version": {
    "number": "8.x.x",
    "build_type": "docker",
    ...
  }
}

# Version-specific vulnerabilities:
# ES < 1.2: CVE-2014-3120 (script execution)
# ES < 1.4.3: CVE-2015-1427 (Groovy sandbox bypass)
# ES < 6.4.3/5.6.13: CVE-2018-17246 (LFI via plugin)
{% endraw %}
</version_fingerprinting>
</reconnaissance>

<unauthorized_access>
<no_authentication>
{% raw %}
# Test basic access:
curl http://target:9200/
# If returns cluster info, no auth required

# Cluster enumeration:
curl http://target:9200/_cluster/health
curl http://target:9200/_cluster/state
curl http://target:9200/_cluster/settings
curl http://target:9200/_nodes

# Index enumeration:
curl http://target:9200/_cat/indices?v
curl http://target:9200/_aliases
curl http://target:9200/_mapping

# Data access:
curl http://target:9200/_search?q=*
curl http://target:9200/{index}/_search?size=1000
curl http://target:9200/{index}/_doc/{id}
{% endraw %}
</no_authentication>

